<p>Charles Barry Hoffmaster, professor emeritus of philosophy at Western University, has died.<span id="more-55467"></span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="wp-image-55468 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/hoffmaster-barry-784x1024.png" alt="" width="383" height="500" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/hoffmaster-barry-784x1024.png 784w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/hoffmaster-barry-230x300.png 230w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/hoffmaster-barry-768x1003.png 768w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/hoffmaster-barry-400x522.png 400w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/hoffmaster-barry.png 896w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 383px) 100vw, 383px" /></p>
<p>Professor Hoffmaster (known in the profession as Barry Hoffmaster), worked mainly in bioethics, normative ethics and the philosophy of law, writing on a wide range of subjects in these areas. He is the co-author of <a href="https://direct.mit.edu/books/monograph/3602/Re-Reasoning-EthicsThe-Rationality-of-Deliberation" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><i>Re-Reasoning Ethics: </i><i>The Rationality of Deliberation and Judgment in Ethics</i></a> (MIT 2017) and the co-editor of several collections. You can learn more about his work <a href="https://philpapers.org/s/Barry%20Hoffmaster" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p>
<p>Hoffmaster joined the <a href="https://www.uwo.ca/philosophy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Department of Philosophy</a> at Western in 1977. He earned his PhD and MA in philosophy from the University of Minnesota, and his undergraduate degree in philosophy from Dartmouth College.</p>
<p>Professor Hoffmaster died on October 26, 2025.</p>
<p>(via Anthony Skelton)</p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2025/10/30/barry-hoffmaster-1947-2025/">Barry Hoffmaster (1947-2025)</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>